UADataType.Description: The FailureReason is an enumeration that provides the primary reason for failure as part of the ResultType.

Field.Name: NOK_REASON_PROGRAM
Field.Description: The failure of the tightening operation is due to the violation of global tightening program limits. Note: Refer OverAllResultValues list in the TighteningResultType instance if this is the failure reason.

Field.Name: NOK_REASON_STEP
Field.Description: The failure of the tightening operation is due to the violation of tightening program step limits. Note: Refer StepResults list in the TighteningResultType instance if this is the failure reason.

Field.Name: NOK_REASON_ERROR
Field.Description: The failure of the tightening operation is due to external factors which are outside the boundary of the tightening operation. Example: Temperature Overheat, Tool Trigger Lost, etc. Note: Refer Errors list in the TighteningResultType instance if this is the failure reason.

uax:Description.uax:Text: The failure of the tightening operation is due to the violation of global tightening program limits. Note: Refer OverAllResultValues list in the TighteningResultType instance if this is the failure reason.
The failure of the tightening operation is due to the violation of tightening program step limits. Note: Refer StepResults list in the TighteningResultType instance if this is the failure reason.

The failure of the tightening operation is due to external factors which are outside the boundary of the tightening operation. Example: Temperature Overheat, Tool Trigger Lost, etc. Note: Refer Errors list in the TighteningResultType instance if this is the failure reason.

UADataType.Description: The Status is an enumeration that indicates whether the operation was successful or not.

uax:Description.uax:Text: The operation is successful.
The operation is not successful.

UADataType.Description: The ViolationType is an enumeration that provides type of limit violation.

Field.Name: ABOVE_LIMIT
Field.Description: The measured value is above the configured limit.

Field.Name: BELOW_LIMIT
Field.Description: The measured value is below the configured limit.

uax:Description.uax:Text: The measured value is above the configured limit.
The measured value is below the configured limit.

UADataType.Description: This structure contains measured times that were generated during the execution of a joining process.

Field.Name: StartTime
Field.Description: Contains the time when the system started execution of the joining process.

Field.Name: EndTime
Field.Description: Contains the time when the system finished (or stopped/aborted) execution of joining process.

Field.Name: AcquisitionDuration
Field.Description: Time spent by the joining system collecting required information.

Field.Name: ProcessingDuration
Field.Description: Time spent by the joining system processing data.

UAVariable.Description: Collects the data type descriptions of http://opcfoundation.org/UA/IJT/
Collects the data type descriptions of http://opcfoundation.org/UA/IJT/

UAVariableType.Description: It is used report errors occurred in the system which are outside the boundaries of the given tightening program.

UAVariable.Description: The optional ErrorId is the system-wide unique identifier of the error in the system. This will be useful if system wants to provide an identifier where user can query the system and get more information for troubleshooting. It can also point to the respective EventId reported if available.
The optional ErrorMessage is user readable text message to describe the error.
The mandatory ErrorType is the classification of type of errors due to external factors.
The optional LegacyError is the application or system specific error code.

UAVariableType.Description: This variable type is to describe common sematic required for variables in a given system.

UAVariable.Description: The optional 0:EngineeringUnits defines the engineering unit of the values.
The optional PhysicalQuantity is to determine the type of the physical quantity associated to a given values.

UAVariableType.Description: The ResultType is a subtype of the BaseDataVariableType. It aggregates the properties of Result data which are reported for a given joining system.

UAVariable.Description: The optional Classification provides information on the classification of the result in the joining system.
The mandatory CreationTime indicates the time when the result was created.
The optional GeneratorAssetId is the identifier of the asset which has generated the result.
The optional IsPartial indicates whether the result is the partial result of a total result.
The optional IsSimulated indicates whether the system was in simulation mode when the joining process created this result.
The optional OperationMode provides information on how the joining process was selected. Refer the following section for the list of values.
The mandatory ProcessingTimes is the collection of different processing times that were needed to create the result.
The optional ReporterAssetId is the identifier of the asset which has reported the result. Refer example below to understand the difference between ReporterAssetId and GeneratorAssetId.
The optional ResultContent is an abstract data type to hold result data created by the selected program.
The mandatory ResultId is the system-wide unique identifier of the result.
The mandatory Status indicates whether the joining operation was successful or not.
The optional StatusDetails provides high level status information in a user-friendly text. This can be left empty for successful operations.

UAVariableType.Description: The TighteningResultType is a subtype of the ResultType. It is used report data associated with Tightening Result and the corresponding measurement values.

UAVariable.Description: The optional AdditionalStatusInformation provides any additional information on the status of the given result in case of failures. It represents a user readable information what was causing the process to be NOK.

The optional Errors is an array of external errors which captures the failures outside the boundary of the tightening program are captured as part of the Errors. It is up to the application to fill in the critical/primary error in the Errors list as top entry.
The mandatory ErrorType is the classification of type of errors due to external factors.

The optional FailingStepResultId is the identifier of the step result which is the primary cause of failure.The optional FailingStepResultId is the identifier of the step result which is the primary cause of failure.

The optional FailureReason is an enumeration which provides the primary reason for failure. If a violation is handled by a rework step resulting in a successful operation, then it is not reported as failure.
The mandatory OverallResultValues is an array of overall result values which contains the measurement values of different quantities like torque, angle, time, etc. based on the tightening program.
The mandatory Value is the measured value of the given result. The values correspond to the physical quantity determined by the PhysicalQuantity property of JoiningDataVariableType.
The optional PhysicalQuantity is to determine the type of the physical quantity associated to a given values.

The optional ResultCode is a vendor/application specific code . It can be up to the system to define few numbers to describe Nine-field code, or derivative of the nine-field matrix, etc. 0 – OK, successful operation.
The optional SequenceNumber is the cyclic counter which is incremented for each result generated.
The optional StepResults is an array of step results corresponding to each step in the tightening program. This parameter is used if the system provides one or more step results.
The mandatory Status indicates if the StepResult is successful or not.
The mandatory StepResultId is the system-wide unique identifier of the step result.
The optional StepResultValues is the set of values which needs to be measured as per the tightening program step.
The mandatory Value is the measured value of the given result. The values correspond to the physical quantity determined by the PhysicalQuantity property of JoiningDataVariableType.
The optional PhysicalQuantity is to determine the type of the physical quantity associated to a given values.
The mandatory TighteningProgramStepId is the system-wide unique identifier of the Tightening Program Step.
The optional TighteningJointId is the system-wide unique identifier of the Tightening Joint corresponding to this result.
The optional TighteningProgramId the system-wide unique Identifier of the Tightening Program configured for generating this result.

The optional TighteningProgramVersionId is the system-wide unique version identifier of the Tightening Program configured for generating this result. This will be unique for every change/update of the given tightening program.
The optional TighteningTrace is a structure to include the TighteningTrace content. This can be NULL or empty and it is up to the application to send this as part of the Tightening Result.
The mandatory ResultId is the system-wide unique identifier of the associated result. This is useful to link Result and Trace instances when the Result and Trace are sent separately.
The mandatory StepTraces is an array of StepTraceType which provides trace content for each step in the given tightening program.
The mandatory NumberOfTracePoints is the total number of trace points to be sent for each quantity.
The optional StartTimeOffset is the offset to the ProcessingTimes.StartTime in the Result instance. This value can be used to order the steps in execution order if same step is run multiple times.
The mandatory StepResultId is the system-wide unique identifier of the associated step result.

The mandatory StepTraceData[] is an array of trace data which contains the samples of different quantities like torque, angle, time, etc. The array size of TraceData should be same for each quantity and that is determined by the NumberOfTracePoints value.
The mandatory Values is an array of trace samples for the given quantity based on PhysicalQuantity property.
The optional PhysicalQuantity is to determine the type of the physical quantity associated to a given values.
The mandatory StepTraceId is the system-wide unique identifier of the step trace.
The mandatory TraceId is the system-wide unique identifier of the Trace.

UAVariableType.Description: It is used to report measurement values of the tightening operation. Those are meant to characterize the quality of the process.

UAVariable.Description: The optional Name is a user readable name of the given measurement value.
The optional ParameterLimits provides lower and upper limit of the measured value as per the tightening program.
The optional ReporterId is the system-wide unique identifier of the parameter configured in the Tightening Program which is being monitored or sampled.

The optional ResultStep provides the step number or name of the tightening program step which has generated the result. This is a tightening program value, but it is added as optional parameter in the result for quick information.
The optional SensorId is the system-wide unique identifier of the sensor which has reported the value.
The optional Status indicates whether the measured value is as per the configured limits and corresponds to a successful result.

The optional TargetValue provides the target value of the specific measurement in the tightening program step. This is a tightening program value, but it is added as optional parameter in the result for quick information.
The optional TracePointIndex is the index to the trace sample array from which corresponds to this specific result.

The optional TracePointTimeOffset is the time offset (in seconds) to point out the absolute time point in the array of trace samples. This may or may not match with an element in the TraceData array. If it is not available in the TraceData array, the value can be visualized in the trace graph via interpolation or some other plotting mechanisms.
The mandatory Value is the measured value of the given result. The values correspond to the physical quantity determined by the PhysicalQuantity property of JoiningDataVariableType.
The optional PhysicalQuantity is to determine the type of the physical quantity associated to a given values.
The optional ValueId is the system-wide unique Identifier of the given value if it is available in the system.
The optional ValueTag is an associated tag to the given measurement value to classify it based on the tightening domain.
The optional ViolationConsequence provides information on the consequence occurred due to the violation of the configurable limits.
The optional ViolationType indicates whether the measured value is above or below the configured limit. It is only relevant if program or step configuration is violated.

UAVariableType.Description: It is used report measurement values corresponding to a given step in the tightening program.

UAVariable.Description: The optional Name is the user readable name of the given step.
The optional StartTimeOffset (in seconds) is the offset to the ProcessingTimes.StartTime in Result, this value can be used to order the steps in execution order if same step is run multiple times.
The mandatory Status indicates if the StepResult is successful or not.
The mandatory StepResultId is the system-wide unique identifier of the step result.
The optional StepResultValues is the set of values which needs to be measured as per the tightening program step.
The mandatory Value is the measured value of the given result. The values correspond to the physical quantity determined by the PhysicalQuantity property of JoiningDataVariableType.
The optional PhysicalQuantity is to determine the type of the physical quantity associated to a given values.
The optional StepTraceId is the system-wide unique identifier of the StepTrace associated to the StepResult.

The optional TighteningProgramStep is the step number or name of the tightening program step. Sometimes the step id is like 2A, 3B based on number of branches. Hence a string place holder is needed instead of number.
The mandatory TighteningProgramStepId is the system-wide unique identifier of the Tightening Program Step.

UAVariableType.Description: This structure is to describe of the trace for a given tightening program step.

UAVariable.Description: The mandatory NumberOfTracePoints is the total number of trace points to be sent for each quantity.
The optional StartTimeOffset is the offset to the ProcessingTimes.StartTime in the Result instance. This value can be used to order the steps in execution order if same step is run multiple times.
The mandatory StepResultId is the system-wide unique identifier of the associated step result.

The mandatory StepTraceData[] is an array of trace data which contains the samples of different quantities like torque, angle, time, etc. The array size of TraceData should be same for each quantity and that is determined by the NumberOfTracePoints value.
The mandatory Values is an array of trace samples for the given quantity based on PhysicalQuantity property.
The optional PhysicalQuantity is to determine the type of the physical quantity associated to a given values.
The mandatory StepTraceId is the system-wide unique identifier of the step trace.

UAVariableType.Description: This structure is to describe of the trace values for a given tightening program step.

UAVariable.Description: The optional Description is an additional text to describe the trace samples.
The optional Name is the user readable name for the given trace.

The optional SensorId is the system-wide unique identifier of the sensor which has reported the values. This will be useful for identifying the sensor when the same set of samples are reported by multiple sensors.
The mandatory Values is an array of trace samples for the given quantity based on PhysicalQuantity property.
The optional PhysicalQuantity is to determine the type of the physical quantity associated to a given values.

UAVariableType.Description: This is a base type to encapsulate common data for a Tightening Trace.

UAVariable.Description: The mandatory ResultId is the system-wide unique identifier of the associated result. This is useful to link Result and Trace instances when the Result and Trace are sent separately.
The mandatory TraceId is the system-wide unique identifier of the Trace.

UAVariableType.Description: This structure is to describe the content of traces for all the steps in the given tightening program.

UAVariable.Description: The mandatory StepTraces is an array of StepTraceType which provides trace content for each step in the given tightening program.
The mandatory NumberOfTracePoints is the total number of trace points to be sent for each quantity.
The optional StartTimeOffset is the offset to the ProcessingTimes.StartTime in the Result instance. This value can be used to order the steps in execution order if same step is run multiple times.
The mandatory StepResultId is the system-wide unique identifier of the associated step result.

The mandatory StepTraceData[] is an array of trace data which contains the samples of different quantities like torque, angle, time, etc. The array size of TraceData should be same for each quantity and that is determined by the NumberOfTracePoints value.
The mandatory Values is an array of trace samples for the given quantity based on PhysicalQuantity property.
The optional PhysicalQuantity is to determine the type of the physical quantity associated to a given values.
The mandatory StepTraceId is the system-wide unique identifier of the step trace.

UAObjectType.Description: This is a general event defined to send any type of errors, alerts, system specific information.

UAVariable.Description: The optional JoiningTechnology is a human readable text to identify which joining technology triggered the event.
The optional SystemSpecificInformation is the specific information from the system like Station Name, or Error or alert or any other information provided by the system.

UAObjectType.Description: This event is to be triggered by the server when the tightening system has a complete or partial result available for the client.

UAVariable.Description: The mandatory Result Variable is an instance of ResultType with required mandatory and optional parameters.
The mandatory CreationTime indicates the time when the result was created.
The mandatory ProcessingTimes is the collection of different processing times that were needed to create the result.
The mandatory ResultId is the system-wide unique identifier of the result.
The mandatory Status indicates whether the joining operation was successful or not.

UAObjectType.Description: This is a generic interface common for all assets in a given Tightening System. The purpose of this interface is to provide a standard way of identification and common information for all the assets. This interface has a standard MachineryItemIdentificationType add-in which can be assigned with MachineIdentificationType or MachineryComponentIdentificationType for a given asset based on the requirement of the system.

UAObject.Description: The GeneralAssetInformation Object is an instance of FolderType to group common parameters for all the assets under TighteningSystemType.

UAVariable.Description: The optional Description is the system specific description of the asset.
The optional ErrorCode is the system specific code for the error occurred.
The optional ErrorMessage is the user readable text of the error reported by the given asset.
The optional ErrorTimestamp is the timestamp when the error occurred in the given asset.
The optional ProductInstanceId is a system-wide unique identifier as GUID to be consistent with other entities like Result, Programs, etc. for ease of automation.
The optional SupplierCode is the SAP or ERP Supplier Code of the asset.
The optional Temperature is the measured temperature of the asset.
The optional Uptime is the total number of hours it has been running since its operational date.

UAObject.Description: The Identification Object, using the standardized name defined in OPC 10000-100, provides identification information about the asset. This is a mandatory place holder and any asset inheriting ITighteningSystemAssetType will replace it with MachineIdentificationType or MachineryComponentIdentificationType.

UAVariable.Description: To be used by end users to store a unique identification in the context of their overall application. Servers shall support at least 40 Unicode characters for the clients writing this value, this means clients can expect to be able to write strings with a length of 40 Unicode characters into that field.

To be used by end users to store a human-readable localized text for the MachineryItem. The minimum number of locales supported for this property shall be two. Servers shall support at least 40 Unicode characters for the clients writing the text part of each locale, this means clients can expect to be able to write texts with a length of 40 Unicode characters into that field.
Indicates in which domain or for what purpose the MachineryItem is used.

A string representation of the revision level of the hardware of a MachineryItem. Hardware is physical equipment, as opposed to programs, procedures, rules and associated documentation. Many machines will not provide such information due to the modular and configurable nature of the machine.
The date, when the MachineryItem was switched on the first time after it has left the manufacturer plant.
A human-readable, localized name of the manufacturer of the MachineryItem.
A globally unique identifier of the manufacturer of the MachineryItem.
A human-readable, localized name of the model of the MachineryItem.
The month in which the manufacturing process of the MachineryItem has been completed. It shall be a number between 1 and 12, representing the month from January to December.

A machine-readable string of the model of the MachineryItem, that might include options like the hardware configuration of the model. This information might be provided by the ERP system of the vendor. For example, it can be used as order information.
A globally unique resource identifier provided by the manufacturer of the MachineryItem.

A string containing a unique production number of the manufacturer of the MachineryItem. The global uniqueness of the serial number is only given in the context of the manufacturer, and potentially the model. The value shall not change during the life-cycle of the MachineryItem.

A string representation of the revision level of a MachineryItem. In most cases, MachineryItems consist of several software components. In that case, information about the software components might be provided as additional information in the address space, including individual revision information. In that case, this property is either not provided or provides an overall software revision level. The value might change during the life-cycle of a MachineryItem.
The year (Gregorian calendar) in which the manufacturing process of the MachineryItem has been completed. It shall be a four-digit number and never change during the life-cycle of a MachineryItem.

UAObject.Description: The optional ServiceInformation Object provides general information on the service operations performed on a given asset.

UAVariable.Description: The optional NextServiceDate is the date of the next planned service.
The optional NumberOfServices is the total number of services taken place till date.
The optional RemainingCycles is the remaining cycles before the service or maintenance. It can go negative if a service is skipped to indicate overshoot cycles.
The optional ServiceCycleCount is the total cycle counter when the last service took place.
The optional ServiceCycleSpan is the maximum allowed number of cycles between two services.
The mandatory ServiceDate is the date of the last service.
The mandatory ServicePlace is the location where the last service took place.
The optional ServiceReminderDays is the number of days before a service reminder should be sent.
The optional Type is a user readable open string to describe the type of sub-component such as network module, etc.
The mandatory Capacity is the nominal capacity of the battery.
The optional ChargeCycleCount is the number of times the battery has been charged since the initial operation date.
The mandatory NominalVoltage is the nominal DC voltage of the battery.
The optional NumberOfTightenings is the total number of operations performed using the battery.

The optional StateOfCharge is the state of charge (SOC) indicator functions as a sort of fuel gauge that displays the usable amount of energy like battery estimates in cellphones and laptops. This helps determine optimal charging and discharging. It is given in percentage.

The optional StateOfHealth is the State of Health is a measurement that reflects the general condition of a battery and its ability to deliver the specified performance compared with a fresh battery. It considers such factors as charge acceptance, internal resistance, voltage, and self-discharge. It is given in percentage.
The optional Type is a user readable text to determine the type of battery based on technology, chemical composition, etc.
The optional CableLength is the length of the cable.
The optional Type is the classification of the cable.
The optional Type is the classification of a Controller.
The optional FeedingSpeed indicates the output in parts per time. Example: fasteners / minute.
The optional FillLevel is the fill level in the feeder in percentage [%]. (0%=empty, 100% = full).
The mandatory Material is the type or name of the part which is supplied by the feeder.
The optional Type is the classification of a Feeder.
The optional StorageCapacity is the static information on size of the storage in Bytes.
The optional Type is the type of memory device. It may define the form factor, interface, or technology. Examples: Flash, CFAST, USB, etc.
The optional UsedSpace is the static information on size of the used space in Bytes.
The optional ActualPower is the actual load consumption of the power supply.
The mandatory InputSpecification is the specification of the power supply. Example: 230 V, 50/60 Hz, 10A.
The optional NominalPower is the maximum output power of the power supply.

UAObject.Description: The optional CalibrationInformation Object is the general information about the calibration performed on the given sensor.

UAVariable.Description: The mandatory CalibrationDate is the date when the last calibration took place.
The optional CalibrationPlace is the location where the last calibration took place.

The optional CertificateUri contains the URI of a certificate of the calibration target in case the calibration target is certified and the information available. Otherwise, the Property should be omitted. The String shall be a URI as defined by RFC 3986. Example: MCE test document.
The optional NextCalibrationDate is the date of the next planned calibration.
The optional SensorScale is the nominal scale of the sensor. It corresponds also with the measurement range of the sensor.
The optional Value is the actual measured value of the sensor.
The optional OverloadCount is the number of overloads of the sensor, where the permissible load of the senor was exceeded.
The optional Type is the classification of a Sensor.
The optional NodeNumber is the node identifier in multiple configurations, e.g. cabinet with one controller and multiple servo/tightening modules.
The optional Type is a user readable open string to describe the type of sub-component such as network module, etc.
The mandatory DesignType provides information on the design of the Tool.
The mandatory DriveMethod provides information on the drive method of the motor of the Tool.
The mandatory DriveType provides information on the drive type of the Tool.
The optional MaxSpeed is the maximum rotation speed of the driving shaft.
The mandatory MaxTorque is the maximum allowed torque for which the tool may be used for tightening processes. For Click Wrenches, it may not be available.
The optional MinTorque is the minimum allowed torque for which the tool may be used for tightening processes.
The optional MotorType is the type of motor in the tool.
The optional ShutOffMethod provides information on the shutoff method of the tool.
The optional TotalNumberOfTightenings is the total number of tightenings executed by the tool. It is incremented by 1 to capture total number of tightenings.
The optional TotalNumberOfTighteningsSinceService is the total number of tightenings executed by the tool since the last service of the tool.
The mandatory Type is the classification of a Tool.

UAObjectType.Description: The TighteningSystemType provides the overview of data exposed from a given tightening system.

UAObject.Description: ResultManagement is an instance of the FolderType to organize standard methods to access result and an optional folder Results which could be used to access result variables in the address space.

uax:Description.uax:Text: With this argument the client can give a hint to the server how long it will need access to the result data. A value > 0 indicates an estimated maximum time for processing the data in milliseconds. A value = 0 indicates that the client will not need anything besides the data returned by the method call. A value < 0 indicates that the client cannot give an estimate. The client cannot rely on the data being available during the indicated time period. The argument is merely a hint allowing the server to optimize its resource management.

The server shall return to each client requesting result data a system-wide unique handle identifying the result set / client combination. This handle should be used by the client to indicate to the server that the result data is no longer needed, allowing the server to optimize its resource handling.
The result including metadata.
0 – OK Values > 0 are reserved for errors defined by this and future standards. Values < 0 shall be used for application-specific errors.
System-wide unique identifier for the result.

With this argument the client can give a hint to the server how long it will need access to the result data. A value > 0 indicates an estimated maximum time for processing the data in milliseconds. A value = 0 indicates that the client will not need anything besides the data returned by the method call. A value < 0 indicates that the client cannot give an estimate. The client cannot rely on the data being available during the indicated time period. The argument is merely a hint allowing the server to optimize its resource management.

The server shall return to each client requesting result data a system-wide unique handle identifying the result set / client combination. This handle should be used by the client to indicate to the server that the result data is no longer needed, allowing the server to optimize its resource handling.
The result including metadata.
0 – OK Values > 0 are reserved for errors defined by this and future standards. Values < 0 shall be used for application-specific errors.

The input time stamp which will be compared to StartTime of the Results. If not empty, results from the given FromTime are returned in the ResultList. Any set of results whose StartTime is greater or equal to FromTime will be returned in the ResultList.

The input timestamp range till the point results should be returned. If not empty, results till the given toTime are returned in the ResultList. Any set of results whose EndTime is less than or equal to ToTime will be returned in the ResultList.
Input to return results based on OK or NOK count. If not empty, results based on the status are returned in the ResultList.
The list of sequence numbers requested from the client. The sequence number is a property of the Tightening Result.
Maximum number of results to return in one call; by passing 0, the client indicates that it does not put a limit on the number of results.
Shall be 0 on the first call, multiples of MaxResults on subsequent calls to retrieve portions of the entire list, if necessary.
Indicates whether there are more results in the entire list than retrieved according to StartIndex and ResultCount.
System wide unique identifier of the asset which reports the results.
System wide unique identifier of the asset which generates the results.
A Boolean flag to notify the application to include list of step results in the ResultList. By default, it is set to false.
A Boolean flag to notify the application to include list of errors in the ResultList. By default, it is set to false.
A Boolean flag to notify the application to include list of traces in the ResultList. By default, it is set to false.

With this argument the client can give a hint to the server how long it will need access to the result data. A value > 0 indicates an estimated maximum time for processing the data in milliseconds. A value = 0 indicates that the client will not need anything besides the data returned by the method call. A value < 0 indicates that the client cannot give an estimate. The client cannot rely on the data being available during the indicated time period. The argument is merely a hint allowing the server to optimize its resource management.
Provides the number of results returned in ResultList in the specific method call.

If filter criteria are provided, it is the total number of results available on the result reporting asset based on the filtering criteria. This value will be same till the IsComplete is set to true if it is based on filter criteria. If NO filter criteria are provided, then it is the total number of results available in the server.

The server shall return to each client requesting result data a system-wide unique handle identifying the result set / client combination. This handle should be used by the client to indicate to the server that the result data is no longer needed, allowing the server to optimize its resource handling.
List of results matching the filter criteria.
0 – OK Values > 0 are reserved for errors defined by this and future standards. Values < 0 shall be used for application-specific errors.
Handle returned by GetResultById or GetResultListFiltered or GetLatestResult, identifying the result set/client combination.
0 – OK Values > 0 are reserved for errors defined by this and future standards. Values < 0 shall be used for application-specific errors.

UAObject.Description: This is an instance of FolderType and is used to organize multiple available results of the tightening system which the server decides to expose in the Address Space. It may contain no results if the server does not expose results in the Address Space at all or if no available result matches the criteria for exposure in the Address Space.

UAVariable.Description: The mandatory CreationTime indicates the time when the result was created.
The mandatory ProcessingTimes is the collection of different processing times that were needed to create the result.
The mandatory ResultId is the system-wide unique identifier of the result.
The mandatory Status indicates whether the joining operation was successful or not.

The optional Description is the description of the system which could be written by the customer to identify the system. It could be the purpose of the system in the assembly line. Examples: Fixtured System, Handheld System, Brake bolt M10 left side, etc.
The optional IntegratorName is the name of the system integrator.
The optional Location is the location of the given system in the given plant or factory in text format.
The mandatory Name is the name or model of the tightening system. It can be provided by the system integrator to identify the system.
The optional SystemId is the system integrator specific identifier for the system. It represents a reference to the manufacturer ERP system to know determine what is the system.
